# Deobfuscated Code & Explanation

## Deobfuscated Version

```javascript
// Constants
var TAU = 6.283;          // 2π (full circle in radians)
var PHI = 1.618;          // Golden ratio
var SQRT_HALF = 0.707;    // √(1/2)

// Physics/simulation configuration
var config = {
    repulsion: 4000,
    compliance: 0.004,
    refractory: 0.92,      // damping/friction factor
    diffusion: 0.0003,     // centering force
    saturation: 40,         // max number of particles
    resistance: 0.04,
    diastole: 0.06          // camera smoothing factor
};

// Nodes in a graph
var nodes = [
    { id: "hub",     label: "Hub",     r: 26, x: 400, y: 300, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: "alpha",   label: "Alpha",   r: 16, x: 500, y: 200, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: "beta",    label: "Beta",    r: 16, x: 300, y: 400, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: "gamma",   label: "Gamma",   r: 14, x: 250, y: 180, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: "delta",   label: "Delta",   r: 14, x: 550, y: 380, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: "epsilon", label: "Epsilon", r: 12, x: 350, y: 150, vx: 0, vy: 0 }
];

// Spring connections (edges) between nodes
var edges = [
    { a: "hub", b: "alpha",   rest: 160, k: 0.006 },
    { a: "hub", b: "beta",    rest: 160, k: 0.005 },
    { a: "hub", b: "gamma",   rest: 170, k: 0.004 },
    { a: "hub", b: "delta",   rest: 170, k: 0.004 },
    { a: "hub", b: "epsilon", rest: 180, k: 0.003 },
    { a: "alpha", b: "beta",  rest: 200, k: 0.002 },
    { a: "gamma", b: "delta", rest: 220, k: 0.002 },
    { a: "alpha", b: "epsilon", rest: 200, k: 0.002 }
];

// Camera state
var camera = { x: 400, y: 300, zoom: 1 };
var cameraTarget = { x: 400, y: 300, zoom: 1 };

// Particle system
var particles = [];
var frameCount = 0;

// Find a node by ID
function findNode(id) {
    for (var i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
        if (nodes[i].id === id) return nodes[i];
    }
    return null;
}

// Physics simulation step
function simulate() {
    // 1. Node-to-node REPULSION (Coulomb's law style)
    for (var i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
        for (var j = i + 1; j < nodes.length; j++) {
            var dx = nodes[i].x - nodes[j].x;
            var dy = nodes[i].y - nodes[j].y;
            var dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) || 1;
            var force = config.repulsion / (dist * dist);
            var fx = (dx / dist) * force;
            var fy = (dy / dist) * force;
            nodes[i].vx += fx;
            nodes[i].vy += fy;
            nodes[j].vx -= fx;
            nodes[j].vy -= fy;
        }
    }

    // 2. Spring ATTRACTION along edges (Hooke's law)
    for (var e = 0; e < edges.length; e++) {
        var nodeA = findNode(edges[e].a);
        var nodeB = findNode(edges[e].b);
        if (!nodeA || !nodeB) continue;

        var dx = nodeB.x - nodeA.x;
        var dy = nodeB.y - nodeA.y;
        var dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) || 1;
        var displacement = dist - edges[e].rest;
        var force = (edges[e].k || config.compliance) * displacement;

        nodeA.vx += (dx / dist) * force;
        nodeA.vy += (dy / dist) * force;
        nodeB.vx -= (dx / dist) * force;
        nodeB.vy -= (dy / dist) * force;
    }

    // 3. Centering GRAVITY + velocity DAMPING + position update
    for (var i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
        nodes[i].vx += (400 - nodes[i].x) * config.diffusion;
        nodes[i].vy += (300 - nodes[i].y) * config.diffusion;
        nodes[i].vx *= config.refractory;  // damping
        nodes[i].vy *= config.refractory;
        nodes[i].x += nodes[i].vx;
        nodes[i].y += nodes[i].vy;
    }
}

// Spawn a new particle from a random node
function spawnParticle() {
    if (particles.length >= config.saturation) return;

    var node = nodes[Math.floor(Math.random() * nodes.length)];
    var angle = Math.random() * TAU;
    var speed = 0.3 + Math.random() * SQRT_HALF;

    particles.push({
        x: node.x,
        y: node.y,
        vx: Math.cos(angle) * speed,
        vy: Math.sin(angle) * speed,
        age: 0,
        maxAge: 800 + Math.random() * 1200,
        size: 0.8 + Math.random() * PHI * SQRT_HALF
    });
}

// Update all particles (move + age + cull)
function updateParticles() {
    for (var i = particles.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
        var p = particles[i];
        p.vx *= 1 - config.resistance * 0.125;
        p.vy *= 1 - config.resistance * 0.125;
        p.x += p.vx;
        p.y += p.vy;
        p.age++;
        if (p.age > p.maxAge) {
            particles.splice(i, 1);
        }
    }
}

// Smooth camera interpolation toward target
function updateCamera() {
    camera.x += (cameraTarget.x - camera.x) * config.diastole;
    camera.y += (cameraTarget.y - camera.y) * config.diastole;
    camera.zoom += (cameraTarget.zoom - camera.zoom) * config.diastole;
}

// Main loop tick
function tick() {
    simulate();
    updateParticles();
    if (frameCount % 3 === 0) spawnParticle();
    updateCamera();
    frameCount++;
}

// Run at ~60fps (16ms interval)
setInterval(tick, 16);
```

## What It Does

This is a **force-directed graph layout simulation** with a particle system — the backend logic for a visualization (no rendering code is included here). Specifically:

### 🔵 Graph Physics (Force-Directed Layout)
- **6 nodes** ("Hub", "Alpha", "Beta", "Gamma", "Delta", "Epsilon") are connected by **8 spring edges**
- **Repulsion**: All nodes repel each other (inverse-square law, like electric charges) to prevent overlap
- **Spring attraction**: Connected nodes are pulled toward each other via Hooke's law with configurable rest lengths and stiffness
- **Centering gravity**: A weak force pulls everything toward the center point (400, 300)
- **Damping**: Velocities are multiplied by 0.92 each frame to prevent infinite oscillation

### ✨ Particle System
- Every 3 frames, a **particle spawns** from a random node and drifts outward at a random angle
- Particles slow down over time (resistance) and are **removed after their lifespan** (800–2000 frames)
- Maximum of **40 particles** at once

### 📷 Camera
- A **smooth-follow camera** that lerps toward its target position/zoom at 6% per frame

### 🎯 Summary
This is the **simulation engine** for an animated, interactive node-graph visualization — likely rendered elsewhere on a canvas. The nodes settle into a balanced layout through competing forces, while ambient particles float away from the nodes for visual flair.
